HEADWORD: Ruta-baga
<hw>Ru`ta-ba"ga</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A kind of turnip commonly with a large and long or ovoid yellowish
root; a Swedish turnip. See <er>Turnip</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rutaceous</ent>⟦br⟧
